jsonxx
------------------------------------------
JSON++ is a light-weight JSON parser, writer and reader written in C++.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.5-1
  libgcc1-13.4.0-1
  libjsonxx-devel-1.0.1-1bl1
  libjsonxx1-1.0.1-1bl1
  libstdc++6-13.4.0-1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.45.1-1
  cmake-4.1.3-1
  cygport-0.37.5-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-13.4.0-1
  ninja-1.13.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/hjiang/jsonxx

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/hjiang/jsonxx/archive/refs/tags/v1.0.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack jsonxx-1.0.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./jsonxx-1.0.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/jsonxx-1.0.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/jsonxx-1.0.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libjsonxx1-1.0.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libjsonxx-devel-1.0.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(jsonxx)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/jsonxx.README
  /usr/share/doc/jsonxx/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/jsonxx/README.md

(libjsonxx1)
  /usr/bin/cygjsonxx-1.dll

(libjsonxx-devel)
  /usr/include/jsonxx.h
  /usr/lib/libjsonxx.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/jsonxx.pc

